{"id":227686996,"title":"Non‚Äêparametric Bayesian Estimation of a Spatial Poisson Intensity","authors":["Juha Heikkinen","Elja Arjas"],"_abstract":"A method introduced by Arjas & Gasbarra (1994) and later modified by Arjas & Heikkinen (1997) for the non-parametric Bayesian estimation of an intensity on the real line is generalized to cover spatial processes. The method is based on a model approximation where the approximating intensities have the structure of a piecewise constant function. Random step functions on the plane are generated using Voronoi tessellations of random point patterns. Smoothing between nearby intensity values is applied by means of a Markov random field prior in the spirit of Bayesian image analysis. The performance of the method is illustrated in examples with both real and simulated data.","cited_in":[{"id":24052917,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/24052917_Image_segmentation_by_polygonal_Markov_Fields"},{"id":223457711,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/223457711_Bayesian_inference_for_spatially_inhomogeneous_pairwise_interacting_point_processes"},{"id":221653841,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/221653841_Finding_simple_intensity_descriptions_from_event_sequence_data"},{"id":227659607,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/227659607_A_shared_component_model_for_joint_and_selective_clustering_of_two_diseases"},{"id":267246629,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/267246629_A_Bayesian_Nonparametric_Approach_to_Inference_for_Spatial_Poisson_Processes"},{"id":47932762,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/47932762_On_probability-based_inference_under_data_missing_by_design"},{"id":228891160,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228891160_A_nonparametric_Bayesian_method_for_assessing_uncertainty_in_thematic_maps_of_forest_variables"},{"id":237539643,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/237539643_Bayesian_multi-dimensional_density_estimation_with_P-splin